 ===========================================================
|                                                           |
|                          BUGS                             |
|                                                           |
 ===========================================================

- Go to any move. Go one move back. Add a comment, let's say "Good move". 
Make a move, choose "Add New Variation". The comment will be repeated. -> KNOWN BUG, let's say it is a feature

- Open any game via Finder. In Recent files, paths contain /./ making it 
possible to have the same file listed twice. -> SEEMS OK

Possible improvements (perhaps not bugs, but awkward)
- Empty variations are not deleted when last move is deleted)

- It is possible to add NAG before the first move of the game/variation. For variations, it is not even visible.

- PGN window with short header ON. If strip first moves -> the game is empty (bug exists in Scid 3.6.1)

- Right click in PGN window does not always display the right position. Happens because of some comments parsing. Bug exists in original Scid 3.6.1

- when clicking quickly on engine's "add move" it will try to add several moves for the same color, hence an error comment in PGN.  Bug exists in original Scid 3.6.1

- sc_game push generates a new game that sc_game pop does not delete. This is used by trial mode and lead to memory leak.

INTERNATIONALIZATION
* bug: correct charset support in Tcl 8.3.x and Tcl 8.4.x -> TO BE FIXED BY USERS OF CHARSETS
* bug: convert from current encoding to UT8 on import -> NO, NEED TO SWITCH TO MSGCAT
* bug: convert from UTF8 to current encoding on export

GAME EDITOR
* bug: with comment editor active browsing the game 'modifies' it -> try to detect that comment editor did not change, so no need to flag game as dirty.

 ===========================================================
|                                                           |
|                     FEATURE REQUESTS                      |
|                                                           |
 ===========================================================

- Add endgame tables support to PPC

- use tablelist package to revamp Game List window

- port FICS canvas to PPC

- FICS : user commands at login

- FICS : 
	* implement timeseal (post a message to MAd -> full box, tried Hawk) Hi, I would like to use timesealing with the port of Scid I made on Pocket PC (I added FICS and Novag Citrine support). Could you give me pointers or a binary that could act as a proxy (ARM processor)?

- Separate remove comments / remove NAGs (often I would like to remove
only comments, leaving NAGs)

- Single command to remove comments+NAGs+variations+nonstandard tags (useful
when exporting/copying a game with copyrighted annotations)

- Remove game(s) from clipboard
You can remove game(s) from filter, but Clipboard can only be emptied, you
cannot remove some games. Such a feature is useful when you choose some games
for exporting. -> workaround open game list and RMB for removing games from filter before export

- Allow setting 'Low CPU priority' for engines by default
This is the case under Windows. Under Linux, a solution is to start engines with prio=5 by default. 
Another solution is to make an option or remember latest setting -> DONE

- Keyboard shortcuts for 'Discard'  / 'Go Back' in 'Leave game' dialog

- Remove icons for adding coordindates/move indicator from standard toolbar.
These are hardly used (user prefers one version or another, he doesn't change
it). Some commonly used functions will be better.

