                   PRIORITY 2
---------------------------------------------------
- Start game analysis at the end of the game to fill hash tables
- Display several score graphs if there are multiple evaluations (sc_game_scores l.7339 of tkscid.cpp)
- remove Ctrl-R and if gn = 0 -> add game , otherwise replace
- vars add at the end of a game
- Engines tournament (with specific opening line ?)
- 6 men EGTB support (http://kd.lab.nig.ac.jp/chess/tablebases-online/)
- export opening report in PGN (and check HTML conversion) : see proc mergeGame l.119 of end.tcl [sc_report opening best a 50]
---------------------------------------------------
                   PRIORITY 3
---------------------------------------------------
- The ability to delete a whole tree from "tree window". To be able to trim undesired moves and games from the database easily.
- book generation from Scid (re-use of Polyglot code)
- The idea of markers on the board to show opening stats is good, but there are still questions that arise :
	- how to show both frequency and score ?
	- is is relevant to show arrows when the number of games played is low (for example under 5) ?
	An idea could be to use colors for scores :
	- green : score > 55%
	- light green : score between 50 and 55 %
	- light red : score between 45 and 50 %
	- red : score < 45%
---------------------------------------------------
                   PRIORITY 9
---------------------------------------------------
- mini board false (seems due to comments in PGN window)
- The ability to save a (layout). So SCID can access often used windows with a menu choice. For example: One (layout) might be "board window" + "tree window" + "engine analysis", and a second (layout) might be any other combination of windows I might choose.


